        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 5:24PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Day Center, or 15 miles southwest of Lake George Village, moving east
at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Gurn Spring, Beartown, French Mountain, Lake Luzerne, Kings Station,
Fourth Lake, Kings, Conklingville, North Greenfield, Porter Corners,
Paradise Beach, Hartman, Corinth, Lake Luzerne-Hadley, West Glens
Falls, Lake Luzerne Campground, West Day, Batchellerville, Fox Hill,
and Allentown.

This includes Interstate 87 between exits 16 and 20.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
east central New York.</instruction>
